1
00:00:00,490 --> 00:00:02,580
<i>I don't want anyone else to have you.</i>

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,490
<i>I want you to be mine.</i>

3
00:00:04,490 --> 00:00:07,200
<i>I ran into a girl I used to like.</i>

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,430
<i>Ever since I hurt you,</i>

5
00:00:09,430 --> 00:00:11,960
it's always been weighing on me.

6
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:13,990
Please, don't worry about it anymore.

7
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:15,730
<i>What do you think of me?</i>

8
00:00:15,730 --> 00:00:17,190
<i>Tell me.</i>

9
00:00:17,190 --> 00:00:19,940
If you don't say it out loud,
I'll get anxious.

10
00:00:19,940 --> 00:00:22,900
I like you, Chiaki.

11
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:26,660
<i>Promise you'll never stop liking me.</i>

12
00:00:28,790 --> 00:00:30,960
<i>I'll always be by your side.</i>

13
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:33,700
Ama, I love you.

14
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:36,420
Really?

15
00:00:36,420 --> 00:00:40,910
Yeah, Director Tanuma asked
if you'd be the heroine's best friend.

16
00:00:40,910 --> 00:00:42,040
I'll do it!

17
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:43,330
Please give me the role!

18
00:00:43,330 --> 00:00:45,980
Alright, I'll pass the word on to them.

19
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:47,040
Good for you.

20
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:48,450
Thank you.

21
00:00:55,930 --> 00:01:02,170
<i>I'm going to appear in Director Tanuma's
movie as the heroine's friend!</i>

22
00:01:07,670 --> 00:01:09,830
[I'm happy for you. You earned this, Ama.]

23
00:01:09,830 --> 00:01:12,510
<i>Everything is going perfectly.</i>

24
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:14,600
<i>Terrifyingly so.</i>

25
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,940
Have a good day.

26
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:19,940
Hey there.

27
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,600
Hello.

28
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,290
Hey...

29
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:26,490
You're dating Chiaki, right?

30
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:28,660
Yes.

31
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:32,090
And you even stood up to his mother for him?

32
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:34,710
You even heard about that?

33
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:37,430
Chiaki told me about it happily.

34
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:45,500
I'm glad someone like you
ended up being Chiaki's girlfriend.

35
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:47,970
Huh?

36
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,040
Oh, it's nothing.

37
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:52,990
Well, see you later!

38
00:01:56,340 --> 00:01:58,120
[The Insomniac Woman's Love Discussion]
[Dressing Room]

39
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:01,240
Chiaki Hosho's that awful?

40
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:03,290
Yeah, a one-and-done kind of guy.

41
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:07,040
- He never keeps a steady girlfriend at all.
- What?

42
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:10,670
But wasn't there a rumor
of him previously dating the model Seira?

43
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:14,320
Seira? The one who went to Hollywood?

44
00:02:17,490 --> 00:02:20,960
<i>I expect nothing less from Chiaki Hosho.</i>

45
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,440
I'm glad to see you.

46
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:29,740
You look well, Chiaki.

47
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:34,880
How about you, Seira? How's life abroad?

48
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:37,100
Every day is full of auditions,

49
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:40,410
but it's way more relaxed
than being in Japan.

50
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:42,620
I see.

51
00:03:05,699 --> 00:03:07,199
What?

52
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:10,860
- Director, hello.
- Hey there.

53
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:13,587
Is that your next project?

54
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:15,863
Yeah. Have a look.

55
00:04:15,863 --> 00:04:17,700
- May I?
- Sure.

56
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:25,110
Wow.

57
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:27,250
Rin's in this too?

58
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,960
The minor roles aren't cast yet.

59
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,510
[Ama Minase]
Gotta cast them quickly.

60
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:33,310
Filming starts soon.

61
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,000
Well...

62
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,620
Director?

63
00:04:46,460 --> 00:04:47,910
Yes?

64
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:50,500
Where are you right now?

65
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:54,510
I'm heading to the cast meeting
for Director Tanuma's movie.

66
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:57,090
I see.

67
00:04:57,090 --> 00:04:59,560
Text me when it's over.

68
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:02,510
Got it.

69
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:06,100
I'm here now.

70
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,740
<i>Alright, do your best.</i>

71
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:11,400
Okay, bye.

72
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,350
Huh?

73
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:21,820
Ama?

74
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:25,010
Huh?

75
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:28,750
Are you in Director Tanuma's movie too?

76
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,970
You're in it too, Kairi-senpai?

77
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:32,700
Yeah.

78
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:37,620
I never thought
we'd get to act together this soon.

79
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:39,180
I'm so surprised.

80
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:41,760
What role are you playing?

81
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,110
Kengo.

82
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,380
Huh?

83
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:49,100
You're playing my lover.

84
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,280
Oh...

85
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,860
I see.

86
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,580
Director,

87
00:05:55,580 --> 00:06:00,570
I hope to appear in this movie too,
even if it's just a tiny part...

88
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:05,290
Well, the producers would be thrilled
if you joined,

89
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:08,000
but you wouldn't take a minor role.

90
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:13,680
No, I really want to join.

91
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,990
Really?

92
00:06:14,990 --> 00:06:16,260
Yes.

93
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:18,850
Anyway!

94
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:20,890
I'll be in your care.

95
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:23,830
Okay. I can't wait.

96
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:25,840
See you soon.

97
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:33,812
[Tanuma Productions]
[Cast Meeting]

98
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:37,710
We want to make this an amazing film,

99
00:06:37,710 --> 00:06:40,430
so everyone, please give us your support.

100
00:06:40,430 --> 00:06:43,160
Let's do our best!

101
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,390
<i>What do I do?</i>

102
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:03,550
<i>Did I do something wrong?</i>

103
00:07:11,550 --> 00:07:14,580
- Excuse me...
- Oh, my God.

104
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:16,090
You're so adorable!

105
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:18,930
- Huh?
- Ms. Minase, you're an idol too, right?

106
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:20,070
Your eyes sparkle!

107
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:22,230
I couldn't look away this whole time!

108
00:07:22,230 --> 00:07:24,060
Hey, cut it out.

109
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,650
You're scaring Ama.

110
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,320
Hey, don't get so chummy.

111
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,980
Do you know her?

112
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:31,800
She was my junior back in school.

113
00:07:32,710 --> 00:07:35,580
Sorry for startling you.

114
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,700
Not at all.

115
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:41,000
I was shocked at how beautiful you are.

116
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,750
I'm going out for drinks
with the Director later.

117
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:46,410
Wanna come along?

118
00:07:46,410 --> 00:07:48,620
Huh? Is that okay?

119
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:50,320
Of course!

120
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:51,888
It's fine, right? Director.

121
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:54,140
- What's up?
- Can she join us for drinks?

122
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,460
Sure, that's fine.

123
00:07:55,460 --> 00:07:56,920
You can come too, Kairi.

124
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,190
Oh, thank you so much.

125
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:06,320
Ama, do you have a boyfriend?

126
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,800
If not, you and I can...

127
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:11,040
Stop! Stop! Stop!

128
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,790
Rin, you're way too drunk!

129
00:08:12,790 --> 00:08:15,320
Quit being clingy and annoying!

130
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:18,100
Some things never change with Rin.

131
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:21,380
Sorry to have kept you waiting.
Here's your order.

132
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,212
- Who ordered this?
- Me.

133
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:25,700
[Mr. Chiaki]
Looks good.

134
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:29,350
- This is so good.
- Excuse me for a moment.

135
00:08:32,930 --> 00:08:34,510
Hello?

136
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:36,510
<i>Where are you?</i>

137
00:08:36,510 --> 00:08:40,230
I'm with the Director
and some cast members for dinner.

138
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:47,520
I told you to contact me when it's over,
remember?

139
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:55,500
Did you forget about me?

140
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,730
<i>Of course not.</i>

141
00:08:57,730 --> 00:08:59,520
<i>I just never got the chance.</i>

142
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:01,730
Come home right now.

143
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:04,400
But, I'm the newest one here.

144
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,370
<i>Where are you?</i>

145
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:08,390
I'm coming to get you.

146
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:10,630
What?

147
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:22,480
Ama?

148
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,420
I'm sorry.

149
00:09:25,420 --> 00:09:26,983
I need to head out now.

150
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:29,036
- Sure.
- Are you leaving?

151
00:09:29,036 --> 00:09:30,200
No!

152
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,760
Rin.

153
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,750
It's alright, Ms. Minase.

154
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:34,950
I'm sorry.

155
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,330
I'm looking forward to working with you.

156
00:09:37,330 --> 00:09:38,940
Sure, likewise!

157
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:05,360
Well, I...

158
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,260
Chiaki?

159
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:36,060
Ama, why can't you understand how I feel?

160
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,460
Huh?

161
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:41,050
Even when we're apart,

162
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:44,760
I'm always thinking about you, Ama.

163
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:48,220
It drives me crazy.

164
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:51,040
But...

165
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,660
you're not like that, huh?

166
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:03,080
I'll be more careful from now on.

167
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:09,830
I'm scared.

168
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:13,330
We're on different sets now.

169
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:18,100
I worry about what you're doing
when I'm not around.

170
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:23,770
I'm such a clingy guy.

171
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,350
That's not true.

172
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:29,010
I know I'm being irrational too.

173
00:11:30,380 --> 00:11:32,170
But,

174
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:35,050
that's how much I love you.

175
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:39,870
I need you to know
how worried I am about you.

176
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:43,310
Okay.

177
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:45,990
I'm sorry.

178
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:48,920
No,

179
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:52,010
I am, too.

180
00:11:53,940 --> 00:11:55,330
I'm sorry.

181
00:12:04,010 --> 00:12:07,020
How was the drinking party?

182
00:12:08,950 --> 00:12:11,820
Ms. Rin livened the party up.

183
00:12:12,450 --> 00:12:15,010
Rin, huh?

184
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:17,510
I've acted with her before.

185
00:12:17,510 --> 00:12:19,530
Really?

186
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:22,260
Who else is in the cast?

187
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:24,560
Come to think of it,

188
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,130
I never asked who your co-star is.

189
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,330
Well...

190
00:12:32,330 --> 00:12:36,430
<i>There's nothing to feel bad about, but...</i>

191
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,550
Here.

192
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,740
Good work.

193
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:43,590
Thank you very much.

194
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,520
Ama?

195
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,540
H-He's a really nice person.

196
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:57,120
But I don't think you know him.

197
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,030
It's just a minor role.

198
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,910
Is that so?

199
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,290
Yeah.

200
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,230
Thank you very much.

201
00:13:19,230 --> 00:13:21,270
Of course.

202
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:23,260
Oh, right. Here.

203
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:25,020
Keep this with you.

204
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:28,230
Huh? Are you sure?

205
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:31,400
Yeah, come see me anytime.

206
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,630
Okay.

207
00:13:35,270 --> 00:13:39,970
And let's share our location on an app
so I can pick you up more easily.

208
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,310
An app?

209
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:44,880
Give me your phone.

210
00:13:56,180 --> 00:13:57,760
Here.

211
00:13:58,630 --> 00:14:02,640
Wow, this is really handy.

212
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:21,140
I really love you.

213
00:14:24,170 --> 00:14:26,350
I love you too.

214
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,370
Don't ever leave me.

215
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:02,950
Either way...

216
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:06,970
I'm not going to let you go.

217
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,250
You're the absolute worst.

218
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,880
Say something already.

219
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,670
Say it!

220
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:20,740
There's... nothing to say.

221
00:15:22,490 --> 00:15:26,070
You always push me away like that.

222
00:15:26,070 --> 00:15:27,640
I'm done.

223
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,792
Cut! Okay!

224
00:15:31,792 --> 00:15:33,141
Cut!

225
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:35,580
Okay! Let's move on to the next scene.

226
00:15:35,580 --> 00:15:39,990
I'm sorry, that hurt, didn't it?

227
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,950
I-I'm so sorry!

228
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,420
I'm just kidding.

229
00:15:46,420 --> 00:15:48,940
You're so easy to fool, Ama.

230
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:51,110
Then I'll hit harder in the next take.

231
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:54,500
Sorry, please keep it at this level.

232
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:05,000
Long time no see, Rin.

233
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,230
Oh, Chiaki.

234
00:16:07,230 --> 00:16:09,960
Still as popular as ever, I see.

235
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,740
Thank you.

236
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,260
Speaking of which,

237
00:16:13,260 --> 00:16:16,423
you're in Director Tanuma's movie, right?

238
00:16:16,423 --> 00:16:17,860
You heard about it?

239
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:20,280
Who else is starring?

240
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,850
Let's see.

241
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:24,930
Nakahara, Mr. Ueda,

242
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:29,610
and there's this adorable girl
who's also an idol named Ama.

243
00:16:29,610 --> 00:16:31,500
Oh...

244
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:34,990
Do you know who her co-star is?

245
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:37,110
Huh? It's Kairi.

246
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:38,460
Why?

247
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:42,200
Kairi?

248
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,110
Kairi Asakura?

249
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:45,180
Yeah.

250
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:49,300
It's surprising such a big star
would take a supporting role.

251
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:53,140
Chiaki?

252
00:16:57,360 --> 00:17:01,110
Ama lied to me.

253
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:07,430
He's a really nice person.

254
00:17:07,430 --> 00:17:10,920
But I don't think you know him.

255
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,891
[Mr. Chiaki]
[Missed Voice Call]

256
00:17:27,460 --> 00:17:30,220
- Hey.
- Hello.

257
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:32,810
You like this, right?

258
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:36,900
I'm surprised you remember, Kairi-senpai.

259
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,300
Hey.

260
00:17:39,220 --> 00:17:43,690
We're not students anymore,
so drop the "senpai".

261
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:46,870
Just call me Kairi.

262
00:17:46,870 --> 00:17:49,880
That's a bit awkward.

263
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:52,230
If you won't call me that,

264
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:56,290
then I won't use your first name anymore.

265
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:00,250
You're being mean again.

266
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:03,920
You've always had that side to you, Kairi.

267
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,800
Just kidding.

268
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:17,230
Hey.

269
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:21,810
Do you have a boyfriend, Ama?

270
00:18:23,370 --> 00:18:26,162
A boyfriend?

271
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,680
You do, huh?

272
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:36,380
Please keep it a secret.

273
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:42,400
What's he like?

274
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,840
An actor?

275
00:18:44,450 --> 00:18:46,070
Yes.

276
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:50,180
He's way too good for me.

277
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:57,520
Who is this actor guy anyway?

278
00:18:57,520 --> 00:19:00,270
I'm definitely more famous than he is.

279
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:07,820
Huh?

280
00:19:07,820 --> 00:19:09,620
What are you doing here?

281
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,660
Where's the filming set?

282
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:23,090
It's over there.

283
00:19:23,090 --> 00:19:24,960
Need the director?

284
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,460
Yeah.

285
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:28,700
Over here.

286
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:33,510
Hey,

287
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:37,380
I told you that I reconnected
with that girl I liked before, right?

288
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:43,450
We started talking again
after she reached out,

289
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:49,570
but I was crushed
to find out she has a boyfriend.

290
00:19:50,450 --> 00:19:53,490
If she's taken, you should give up.

291
00:19:53,490 --> 00:19:55,140
Huh?

292
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:58,290
Wait a second, Chiaki!

293
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:03,920
I thought you liked the challenge.
You're a pro at stealing girls.

294
00:20:05,610 --> 00:20:08,320
I've reflected. It's not a good thing to do.

295
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:10,860
Wow...

296
00:20:10,860 --> 00:20:14,390
You must really love your current girlfriend.

297
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,080
Actually...

298
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:23,100
that girl is my co-star.

299
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:28,320
What?

300
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,860
I hurt her.

301
00:20:40,130 --> 00:20:43,280
Now that we're acting and getting close,

302
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:45,250
this is my chance...

303
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,600
The girl you hurt...

304
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,600
Was it Ama?

305
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:54,190
Huh?

306
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:55,880
You know Ama?

307
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:05,150
Get up.

308
00:21:05,150 --> 00:21:07,200
I'll kill you.

309
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:13,800
Could it be that you're...

310
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:21,200
- Hey, what are you doing?
- This is crazy!

311
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,960
- Let go!
- Chiaki!

312
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:31,040
This guy hurt you, right?

313
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:38,220
That's why I'm gonna kill him.

314
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,341
Stop!

315
00:21:43,341 --> 00:21:44,710
Just get off him!

316
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:47,030
Please don't!

317
00:21:55,780 --> 00:21:57,650
Chiaki!

318
00:22:09,966 --> 00:22:12,146
Why did you lie to me?

319
00:22:15,886 --> 00:22:17,686
It's because...

320
00:22:22,683 --> 00:22:25,913
There's no way
I wouldn't know who Kairi is.

321
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:37,000
I'm so sorry.

322
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,530
I didn't want to make you anxious.

323
00:22:51,060 --> 00:22:52,840
Chiaki?

324
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,360
No, stop!

325
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:06,090
Please.

326
00:23:06,090 --> 00:23:09,370
No, no, stop.

327
00:23:09,370 --> 00:23:12,810
Chiaki, stop, please.

328
00:23:26,849 --> 00:23:29,669
I should've done this sooner,

329
00:23:30,430 --> 00:23:32,217
to make you mine alone.

330
00:23:35,490 --> 00:23:37,730
I'll never let you go until the day I die.

331
00:23:37,730 --> 00:23:39,178
I want to break up.

332
00:23:39,178 --> 00:23:41,350
Chiaki was the boyfriend all along.

333
00:23:41,350 --> 00:23:43,520
If Ama ever belongs to anyone but me,

334
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,000
I want to die with her.

335
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,670
Don't touch Ama, don't get near her.

336
00:23:47,670 --> 00:23:50,520
Die, die, die!

